        <property name="note">
            <value>The dialogue events are kind of crazy.

Basically, a given character's dialogue event will play/loop for the entire duration of a conversation for which that character is present.

The portrait shown next to each line of dialogue in-game drives the &quot;dialogue_portrait&quot; parameter in FMOD, which then throws the event's playhead to the correct emotional state on the timeline.

Once the playhead arrives at a given emotion, we've got transitional &quot;hubs&quot; in place that do a pretty decent job of semi-randomly cycling through conversational syllables for each emotion.

Once the text draw finishes for that line of dialogue, the &quot;dialogue_end&quot; parameter is thrown to 1, and the playhead returns to an idling standby state.



This is one of the more complex systems we've got going on in FMOD, so feel free to watch the video for a deeper understanding of how this all works.</value>
        </property>
